title: Toxicogenomics of nevirapine-associated cutaneous and hepatic adverse events among populations of African, Asian, and European descent

annotation.Notes: Cutaneous adverse events were associated with CYP2B6 516G→T (OR 1.66, all).
annotation.Sentence: CYP2B6 516G→T is associated with increased cutaneous adverse events nevirapine among HIV-infected adults.
Citations: Cutaneous adverse events were associated with CYP2B6 516G→T (OR 1.66, all)...
The association with 516G→T was particularly strong in Blacks, in whom the OR for 516TT homozygosity relative to 516GG homozygosity was 5.92 [95% confidence interval (CI) 1.53-26.8].
Among patients with at least 150 CD4 T cells/μl, polymorphisms in drug metabolism and immune response pathways were associated with greater likelihood of risk for nevirapine-related adverse events.

annotation.Notes: Cutaneous adverse events were associated with CYP2B6 516G→T (OR 1.66, all).
annotation.Sentence: CYP2B6 516G→T is associated with increased cutaneous adverse events nevirapine among HIV-infected adults.
Citations: Cutaneous adverse events were associated with CYP2B6 516G→T (OR 1.66, all)...
The association with 516G→T was particularly strong in Blacks, in whom the OR for 516TT homozygosity relative to 516GG homozygosity was 5.92 [95% confidence interval (CI) 1.53-26.8].
Among patients with at least 150 CD4 T cells/μl, polymorphisms in drug metabolism and immune response pathways were associated with greater likelihood of risk for nevirapine-related adverse events.

annotation.Notes: HLA-Cw*04 was significantly associated with cutaneous adverse events among all study participants, most notably in Blacks and Asians (OR 2.51, all).
annotation.Sentence: HLA-Cw*04 is associated with increased cutaneous adverse events nevirapine among HIV-infected adults.
Citations: Cutaneous adverse events were associated with CYP2B6 516G→T (OR 1.66, all), HLA-Cw*04 (OR 2.51, all), and HLA-B*35 (OR 3.47, Asians; 5.65, Thais).
HLA-Cw*04 was significantly associated with cutaneous adverse events among all study participants, most notably among Blacks and Asians (OR 2.51, all).
Risk for cutaneous adverse events was particularly high among Blacks with CYP2B6 516TT and HLA-Cw*04 (OR 18.90) and Asians with HLA-B*35 and HLA-Cw*04 (OR 18.34).

annotation.Notes: HLA-B*35 was strongly associated with cutaneous adverse events in Asian and Thai participants (OR 3.47, Asians; 5.65, Thais).
annotation.Sentence: HLA-B*35 is associated with increased cutaneous adverse events nevirapine among HIV-infected adults.
Citations: Cutaneous adverse events were associated with CYP2B6 516G→T (OR 1.66, all), HLA-Cw*04 (OR 2.51, all), and HLA-B*35 (OR 3.47, Asians; 5.65, Thais).
Among Asians, but not Blacks or Whites, the OR for cutaneous adverse events was markedly increased among those carrying both HLA-Cw*04 and HLA-B*35 (OR 18.34, 95% CI 5.10-65.99).
This study confirmed strong associations between HLA-B*35, HLA-Cw*04, and cutaneous adverse events among Asians, particularly in Thai participants.

annotation.Notes: HLA-DRB*01 was significantly associated with hepatic adverse events in Whites (OR 3.02, Whites).
annotation.Sentence: HLA-DRB*01 is associated with increased hepatic adverse events nevirapine among HIV-infected adults.
Citations: Hepatic adverse events were associated with HLA-DRB*01 (OR 3.02, Whites), but not CYP2B6 genotypes.
*HLA-DRB1*01* was significantly associated with hepatic adverse events in Whites.

In analyses that excluded individuals with coincident cutaneous and hepatic adverse events, OR for hepatic adverse events among Whites increased from 3.02 to 3.63 for *HLA-DRB1*01.*"]}   Assistant has stopped speaking, and hands back control to the User. annotation.Notes: The frequency of the HLA-B*35 allele was greater in those with nevirapine-related hepatic adverse events as compared to healthy controls when considering a Thai population. No significant results were seen for Asians (non-Thai), Blacks or Whites (p corrected = 0.053, 1.0, 1.0, respectively). Note that this annotation was done on HLA-B*35:01:01:01 because this was the first *35 allele discovered. p-value corrected for multiple testing.
annotation.Sentence: HLA-B *35:01 is associated with increased risk of Drug Toxicity when treated with nevirapine in people with HIV Infections.

annotation.Notes: The frequency of the HLA-DRB1*01 allele was greater in those with nevirapine-related hepatic adverse events as compared to healthy controls when considering a White population. No significant results were seen for Asians or Blacks. Note that this annotation was done on HLA-DRB1*01:01:01 because this was the first *01 allele discovered. p-value corrected for multiple testing.
annotation.Sentence: HLA-DRB1 *01:01 is associated with increased risk of Drug Toxicity when treated with nevirapine in people with HIV Infections.

annotation.Notes: The frequency of the HLA-Cw*04 allele was greater in those with nevirapine-related cutaneous adverse events as compared to healthy controls. Note that this annotation was done on HLA-C*04:01:01:01 because this was the first *04 allele discovered. p-value corrected for multiple testing.
annotation.Sentence: HLA-C *04:01 is associated with increased risk of Drug Toxicity when treated with nevirapine in people with HIV Infections.

annotation.Notes: The frequency of the C allele was greater in those with nevirapine-related cutaneous adverse events as compared to healthy controls. This SNP was in LD with rs2054674 (r2 = 0.982) and rs3745274 (r2 > 0.90). p-value corrected for multiple testing. This SNP was not associated with hepatic adverse events after correcting for multiple comparisons.
annotation.Sentence: Allele C is associated with increased risk of Drug Toxicity when treated with nevirapine in people with HIV Infections.
